   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_196279_1837_11_10_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1837-11-10">Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 10<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> 1837</date>
               </dateline>
               <lb/>
               <salute>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Sir</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I am much obliged by your<lb/>
               present of the  New Edition<lb/>
               of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Lette2">
                  <persName ref="./Personorgraphy.xml#MontM1">Lady Mary W. Montagu</persName>s<lb/>
                  works</title>. - The biographical<lb/>
               <del>notice</del>
               <add>anecdotes</add> prefixed by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StuaL1">Lady Louisa<lb/>
                  Stuart</persName> is remarkably well<lb/>
               written interesting, and<lb/>
               entertaining. -<lb/>
               I have requested my<lb/>
               brother in law <persName ref="./Personorgraphy.xml#WilsL2"> M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Lestock<lb/>
                  Wilson</persName> to answer you for<lb/>
               me respecting the new <choice>
                  <orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>Edition</reg>
               </choice>
               <lb/>
               of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> in the Standard Novels<lb/>
               which you propose. -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Sir</persName>
               <lb/>
               Your obliged amp<lb/>
               humble servant<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
            </closer>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_196279_1837_11_10_page02.jpg"/>
